If a `VPInstruction` with an underlying value is replaced by a `VPInstruction` without an underlying value, it might fail to create widen/replicate recipes later.
But `simplifyRecipes` is called on `VPlan0` (before widening) AND on widened VPlans.
If it's called on `VPlan0`, and it replaces a `VPInstruction` (which wraps an IR instruction) with a new `VPInstruction` without an underlying value, then later when `tryToConvertVPInstructionsToVPRecipes` is called, it will skip it:
